      "year": 2024,
      "abstract": "In Constitutional Public Reason, Wojciech Sadurski contributes to our understanding of constitutional liberal democracy by bringing together public reason, constitutional theory, and detailed constitutional law in a powerful and productive way. Sadurski\u2019s account of public reason, one that is in many important respects different from John Rawls\u2019s own account, correctly recognises the mutability of the content of public reason. I argue that the recognition of the mutability of the content of public reason, however, puts pressure on Sadurski\u2019s characterisation of the relationship between courts and public reason.",
